    {
      "id": "legacy_note_text",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 492,
      "y": 410,
      "width": 650,
      "height": 185,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#374151",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1014,
      "version": 1,
      "versionNonce": 10014,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1770000000014,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "What still remains legacy / as-is\n\n1. UI and config entry still talk in legacy provider IDs such as 'claude-code' and 'kiro-cli'.\n2. buildApiHandler() still resolves provider -> runtimeId -> legacyProvider, so provider semantics still leak upward.\n3. Runtime-specific handlers still exist as dedicated classes: ClaudeCodeHandler, KiroCliHandler.\n4. PersistenceBoundary currently governs config / credentials / probe metadata, not full runtime session memory.\n\nSo: the architecture is no longer single-path as-is, but it is not yet a fully runtime-native system end-to-end.",
      "fontSize": 18,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "baseline": 17,
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "What still remains legacy / as-is\n\n1. UI and config entry still talk in legacy provider IDs such as 'claude-code' and 'kiro-cli'.\n2. buildApiHandler() still resolves provider -> runtimeId -> legacyProvider, so provider semantics still leak upward.\n3. Runtime-specific handlers still exist as dedicated classes: ClaudeCodeHandler, KiroCliHandler.\n4. PersistenceBoundary currently governs config / credentials / probe metadata, not full runtime session memory.\n\nSo: the architecture is no longer single-path as-is, but it is not yet a fully runtime-native system end-to-end.",
      "lineHeight": 1.22
    },
